'''The Free-Flight Dance Dome''' was an elegant bistro on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Etti IV/Legends|Etti IV]].

The establishment served as a meeting place between [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] and [[Ploovo Two-For-One/Legends|Ploovo Two-For-One]] and his guards, but unfortunately the meeting ended in a [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] fight. Han Solo was able escape using a [[Artificial gravity generator/Legends|gravity-shifter]] that the club used to lighten the [[Gravity/Legends|gravity]] and allow its patrons to float. Han Solo turned the gravity on three-times normal gravity while in a protected area. With every patron flattened on the ground from their own intense weight, he and Chewbacca were able to escape through a path unaffected by the change in gravity.

{{Struct-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
''[[A Guide to the Star Wars Universe, Second Edition, Revised and Expanded]]'', in its entry about the Free-Flight Dance Dome, sources the information as coming from the novel ''[[Han Solo's Revenge]]'' while it was really from ''[[Han Solo at Stars' End]]''.

